// The `prelude.reflection` sub-module: agents as first-class, inspectable values. Called qualified
// via the default import — `reflection.get_metadata`, `reflection.call_agent`, type
// `reflection.agent_metadata`.
//
// The two primitives close one loop: `get_metadata` reads a callable's public signature (so an AI
// can be shown what a tool accepts) and `call_agent` dispatches a callable value with a
// runtime-built argument (so an AI's pick can be invoked). Callables whose public signature is
// decided at RUNTIME — an MCP server's tools (`prelude.mcp`) — are minted by the runtime itself and
// participate in both exactly like compiled agents: a tool IS an agent.
//
// `get_metadata` derives a callable value's public signature — its qualified name, its `@"..."`
// description, and the JSON Schemas of its input / output / requests, each schema already a `json`
// value. To assemble a tool list, build the surrounding document explicitly with the `json`
// constructors, embedding each schema as a subtree — e.g.
// `json.json_object(entries = { name = json.json_string(value = m.name), input_schema = m.input })`.
// (Do NOT wrap it with `json.encode`: `encode` embeds a `json` value as its tagged wire form like any
// other `data` value, so it would double-tag the schema rather than pass it through.)
//
// `call_agent` dispatches a callable VALUE with a runtime-built argument record — the
// dynamic-dispatch counterpart of a static call, for a target an AI picked out of a tool list. The
// runtime validates every delegation's argument against the callee's input schema, so malformed args
// throw `call_error` at the call site rather than corrupting the callee — an AI-driven tool loop can
// catch it and let the model retry with corrected arguments.

@"The public metadata of one callable: its (qualified) name, its `@\"...\"` description, and the JSON
Schemas of its input, output and requests — each schema a `json` value, ready to embed in an AI tool
list. A local (closure) callable has an empty name."
data agent_metadata(
  name: string,
  description: string,
  input: json.json,
  output: json.json,
  requests: json.json,
)

@"Derive `agent_metadata` from a callable value (a top-level agent, a data constructor, a request, an
external, a local closure, or a runtime-minted tool such as an MCP server's). A generic callable
instantiated with `[T]` yields schemas specialised to the instantiation; a runtime-minted tool yields
the name / description / input schema its provider declared."
primitive agent get_metadata(value: agent never -> unknown with all) -> agent_metadata

@"A dynamic dispatch failed before the target ran: the target is not a callable, or `args` does not
conform to its input schema (`message` names the offending path). Thrown by `call_agent`."
data call_error(message: string)

@"Invoke a callable VALUE with a runtime-built argument record — dynamic dispatch for a target an AI
picked out of a tool list. `args` is validated against the target's input schema at the delegation
boundary; a mismatch throws `call_error` at this call site (catch it to let the model retry). The
target's effects flow through unchanged."
primitive agent call_agent[R, effect E](target: agent never -> R with E, args: unknown) -> R with E | prelude.throw[call_error]
